SECTION  EMPLOYMENT_HISTORY
  Client: Mercy Health Jan 2024 – Present
  Role: Software Consultant -Workday
  Responsibilities:
  Configured and customized Workday HCM modules, including Compensation, Benefits, Time Tracking, and
  Absence Management, to align with organizational policies.
  Implemented Workday Orchestrations to automate payroll processing and benefits enrollment, improving
  accuracy and efficiency.
  Designed and configured Workday Payroll integrations with ADP, ensuring seamless multi-state payroll
  operations.
  Configured Workday Compensation structures, including bonus plans, merit increases, and stock options,
  improving employee satisfaction.
  Built and tested robust payroll integrations, including ADP Pay force and Fidelity investment data transfer,
  ensuring accurate payroll processing across multiple states.
  Developed and implemented security configurations, ensuring secure access controls and compliance with
  SOX and GDPR.
  Created Supervisory Organization, Re-Organization, Matrix Organization, Subordinate Organization,
  Locations, Positions, Region, Cost centers, Staffing models, Jobs, Position and Compensation.
  Work closely with internal and external teams to build data integration solutions for ERP systems. Used
  functions such as ETV/XTT to do XSLT file transformations for integrations on workday cloud.
  Developed Payroll ADP Payforce Integration, ADP tax Monthly, ADP tax Quarterly, and ADP Periodic
  using Connectors, which are pre-delivered by Workday.
  Generated and validated Workday report, created analysis report and dashboard for Management review.
  Worked on Compensation eligibility rules creation, compensation plan, and compensation package.
  Worked on validating the compensation grades and profiles with the eligibility rules for the hires in different
  geography.

  Client: American Financial Group Nov 2017 – Feb 2022
  Role: Technical Consultant -Workday
  Responsibilities:
  Collaborate closely with clients to understand their unique business processes and requirements, ensuring
  alignment with Workday capabilities and best practices.
  Configure business processes, security roles, and compensation eligibility rules to streamline HR operations
  across regions.
  Implemented Workday Extend solutions to automate HR service requests and payroll adjustments
  Design and configure advanced compensation structures and benefits packages within Workday, tailored to
  meet specific organizational needs and compliance requirements.
  Built custom reports using Report Writer and BIRT for payroll reconciliation, headcount analysis, and
  compliance reporting.
  Created XML and XSLT transformations for document generation and data manipulation, ensuring
  compatibility with vendor systems.
  Designed and implemented inbound integrations for onboarding and benefits enrollment, utilizing Workday
  APIs and external web services.
  Conducted root cause analysis for complex integration failures and implemented solutions that reduced error
  rates by 25%.
  Developed and deployed end-to-end integrations using Workday Studio, EIBs, and Core Connectors for
  Benefits, Payroll, and Compensation processes.
  Collaborated with business stakeholders to identify system requirements and align solutions with business
  objectives.
  Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to develop and execute comprehensive data governance
  strategies within Workday, ensuring data accuracy, integrity, and security.
  Analyse and interpret data from Workday reports and analytics to provide actionable insights and
  recommendations to stakeholders and senior management.
  Conduct performance tuning and optimization of Workday configurations to enhance system responsiveness,
  efficiency, and scalability.
  Create and maintain comprehensive project documentation, including design documents, technical
  specifications, test plans, and user guides, to support effective project management and knowledge transfer.
